                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13528153" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 10 Dec 2012 18:41:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a naive patch that call Auth.setup() only once we know it will work. I however suspect that the authenticator and authorizer should be setup much sooner than that. So the right approach is probably to split that setup() into two methods, but I&apos;ll wait for someone knowledgeable of the Auth thingy to confirm out of laziness.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13528171" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 10 Dec 2012 18:53:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right, IAuthenticator#setup and IAuthorizer#setup should be called before that (where Auth#setup used to be), but superuser part should be scheduled after commit-log replay.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13528201" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 10 Dec 2012 19:31:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Auth.setupSuperuser needs to be called in the &apos;isSurveyMode&apos; of joinRing too, but otherwise +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13528210" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 10 Dec 2012 19:40:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
